your sinister smile,
your brutal lips,
they always speak lies

"don't ask for help"
"it's okay to harm yourself"
"stay in darkness, inflict injuries and scars,
it's less scary than how fake these people are"

silly me, lured into your trap again
burning to ashes, screaming in pain
when like everyone else, i'm about to lose myself too
you come and whisper in my ear, "i'm here for you"

here i am, alone, with you in my mind,
whether it be this room, or my brain, i've been confined
i suddenly realize that i want to cry
but not a tear comes out of my eyes

Your voice comes again, and i hear you say
"dont worry, you've lost nothing, don't miss those days"
i've believed you for days, months and years
maybe that's why i've given up on fighting my fears

you say i've lost nothing but i know the truth
i've lost
my smile,
my tears,
my laugh,
my fears,
my senses,
my sleep,
my friends,
my belief

have i really lost these things?
or have i actually lost myself in this chain?
please, my demons, i need you to get lost
so that i can find myself again"

"there's a blank page
waiting to be filled with colors
i lift up my pen in order to write
should i let them see my brain's sight?

i write, scribble, and throw away the page
i don't want them to know about the cage
but no one would listen, so i decide to write
even though, inside me, there's a fight

the blank white page is now filled with colors
with dark, ashy and watery hues
my tears let the ink dissolve on the surface
funny how even with all these colors, it's still colorless

been silent for hours in order to write
but in reality, has it really been only some hours?
i write, write and write again
trying not to show everything inside my brain

now that my words have been woven together
just like my lips have been, too
the only difference would be that they create beautiful art
while my silence paints my heart black, and rips it apart"

"In a room,
with about hundred other people here
my eyes red,
hoping that i can somehow disappear
my smile bright,

my eyes filled with light,
hoping my life was as bright
looking at others,

into my own little world
where i'm considered normal..
i'm hoping i'm considered normal.
because i'm trying to fit in
even when my thoughts pull me back
even if someone tries to help me,
i feel my heart crack
knowing they're wasting their time on me,
i'm probably giving up, they should give up on me too

i'm about to lose myself
cause even when i'm in this crowded room
neither others find me, nor i seem to find myself.."
